	<item>
		<title>By: peter oram</title>
		<link>http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/improvisation/shape-shifting-chord-changes.html#comment-4305</link>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[peter oram]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Sun, 24 Feb 2013 14:27:15 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://scottsbasslessons.com/?p=3939#comment-4305</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[i like this in principle, but in practice i find voice-leading problems can crop up.  e.g ( in key of C for ex) the F in the iv chord is of course the 7th of the V7, which has more or less got to fall to the 3rd of the tonic chord (i.e. f to e) But this movement is almost certain to be happening in one of the other instruments above the bass, thus we have a perfect trap for not very pleasant side effects like parallel octaves and doubled maj 3rds, and also risks weakening that very powerful bond that is the main point of the perfect cadence  because the note 5 to note one (or in V inversions note 7 or note 2 to note one) movement the gives the cadence its strength   is in danger of turning into the more static feel of a plagal cadence  - albeit with a minor iv chord. how do you suggest maintaining the V-I bond in this situation?

pete]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>i like this in principle, but in practice i find voice-leading problems can crop up.  e.g ( in key of C for ex) the F in the iv chord is of course the 7th of the V7, which has more or less got to fall to the 3rd of the tonic chord (i.e. f to e) But this movement is almost certain to be happening in one of the other instruments above the bass, thus we have a perfect trap for not very pleasant side effects like parallel octaves and doubled maj 3rds, and also risks weakening that very powerful bond that is the main point of the perfect cadence  because the note 5 to note one (or in V inversions note 7 or note 2 to note one) movement the gives the cadence its strength   is in danger of turning into the more static feel of a plagal cadence  &#8211; albeit with a minor iv chord. how do you suggest maintaining the V-I bond in this situation?</p>
<p>pete</p>
]]></content:encoded>
